text: Agurda () is a rural locality (a village) in Baishevsky Selsoviet, Zianchurinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 89 as of 2010. There is 1 street. == Geography == It is located 107 km from Isyangulovo, 10 km from Baishevo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Zianchurinsky District
title: Agurda
